<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Recovery" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Recovery,</orth> 1) the act of gaining or conquering again: <cit><quote>the r. of this drum,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 4.1.38" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 1, 38</bibl></cit>. <emph>they</emph> (the counties) <cit><quote>are past r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.116" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 116</bibl></cit>. <emph>fine and r.,</emph> a term of law: <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.225" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 225</bibl>.* <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.114" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 114</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.114" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 114</bibl> cf. <emph>Fine.</emph><lb />2) restoration from illness or swooning: <bibl n="shak. err 5.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.42" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.5.45" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 5, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.3.188" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 3, 188</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 1, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 1, 54</bibl>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>